{"can_edit": true, "from": {"name": "Santosh Mitra", "id": "676250305810333"}, "subject": "Things to do after installing Fedora 20 (Assuming the installation is done from the 4.3 GB Fedora 20, i386 Installation ISO.)", "updated_time": "2014-03-29T14:51:16+0000", "can_delete": true, "created_time": "2014-03-29T14:51:16+0000", "message": "<p><b>1. Install &quot;Russian Fedora&quot; Reposotories (Needed for VLC, Rosa Media Player etc):</b></p><p><br />sudo yum localinstall <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmirror.yandex.ru%2Ffedora%2Frussianfedora%2Frussianfedora%2Ffree%2Ffedora%2Freleases%2F20%2FEverything%2Fi386%2Fos%2Frussianfedora-free-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm&amp;h=3AQG6HgK2&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/mirror.yandex.ru\\/fedora\\/russianfedora\\/russianfedora\\/free\\/fedora\\/releases\\/20\\/Everything\\/i386\\/os\\/russianfedora-free-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fmirror.yandex.ru\\u00252Ffedora\\u00252Frussianfedora\\u00252Frussianfedora\\u00252Ffree\\u00252Ffedora\\u00252Freleases\\u00252F20\\u00252FEverything\\u00252Fi386\\u00252Fos\\u00252Frussianfedora-free-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm&amp;h=3AQG6HgK2&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://mirror.yandex.ru/fedora/russianfedora/russianfedora/free/fedora/releases/20/Everything/i386/os/russianfedora-free-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm</a></p><p><br />sudo yum localinstall <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmirror.yandex.ru%2Ffedora%2Frussianfedora%2Frussianfedora%2Fnonfree%2Ffedora%2Freleases%2F20%2FEverything%2Fi386%2Fos%2Frussianfedora-nonfree-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm&amp;h=eAQGmevlx&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/mirror.yandex.ru\\/fedora\\/russianfedora\\/russianfedora\\/nonfree\\/fedora\\/releases\\/20\\/Everything\\/i386\\/os\\/russianfedora-nonfree-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fmirror.yandex.ru\\u00252Ffedora\\u00252Frussianfedora\\u00252Frussianfedora\\u00252Fnonfree\\u00252Ffedora\\u00252Freleases\\u00252F20\\u00252FEverything\\u00252Fi386\\u00252Fos\\u00252Frussianfedora-nonfree-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm&amp;h=eAQGmevlx&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://mirror.yandex.ru/fedora/russianfedora/russianfedora/nonfree/fedora/releases/20/Everything/i386/os/russianfedora-nonfree-release-20-1.R.noarch.rpm</a><br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><b>2. Install &quot;RPM Fusion&quot; Repositories (Needed for Unrar, Xine, Audacity etc):</b></p><p><br />su -c &#039;yum localinstall --nogpgcheck <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fdownload1.rpmfusion.org%2Ffree%2Ffedora%2Frpmfusion-free-release-%24&amp;h=lAQF3zoba&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/download1.rpmfusion.org\\/free\\/fedora\\/rpmfusion-free-release-$&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fdownload1.rpmfusion.org\\u00252Ffree\\u00252Ffedora\\u00252Frpmfusion-free-release-\\u002524&amp;h=lAQF3zoba&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://download1.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/rpmfusion-free-release-$</a>(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fdownload1.rpmfusion.org%2Fnonfree%2Ffedora%2Frpmfusion-nonfree-release-%24&amp;h=IAQHPBaMS&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/download1.rpmfusion.org\\/nonfree\\/fedora\\/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;http:\\/\\/l.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=http\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fdownload1.rpmfusion.org\\u00252Fnonfree\\u00252Ffedora\\u00252Frpmfusion-nonfree-release-\\u002524&amp;h=IAQHPBaMS&amp;s=1&quot;);\">http://download1.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$</a>(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm&#039;</p><p><br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><b>3. Install everything from the 4.3 GB Fedora 20 installation ISO:</b></p><p><br /><b>Step 01:</b> Create a empty directory &#039;F20_ISO&#039; in &#039;/mnt&#039; ($ sudo mkdir /mnt/F20_ISO), <br />\u00a0\u00a0 needed for mounting the ISO.<br /><br /><b>Step 02: </b>Assuming the ISO is located in - /home/soham/BackUps/ISOs, mount the ISO:<br />\u00a0\u00a0 <b>$ sudo mount /home/soham/BackUps/ISOs/Fedora-20-i386-DVD.iso /mnt/F20_ISO/</b><br /><br /><b>Step 03: </b>Now we need to create a fake repo &#039;fedora-dvd.repo&#039; in /etc/yum.repos.d with the followings:<br /><b>\u00a0\u00a0 $ sudo leafpad /etc/yum.repos.d/fedora-dvd.repo</b><br />\u00a0\u00a0 Copy/Paste the following:<br /><br /><b>[fedora-dvd]</b><br /><b>name=Fedora DVD $releasever \u2013 $basearch</b><br /><b>failovermethod=priority</b><br /><b>baseurl=file:///mnt/F20_ISO</b><br /><b>enabled=1</b><br /><b>metadata_expire=7d</b><br /><b>gpgcheck=1</b><br /><b>gpgkey=file:///etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-fedora-$basearch</b><br /><br />Save the file and exit Leafpad.<br /><br /><b>Step 04: </b>Now press &#039;ALT+F2&#039;, type the command: gpk-prefs (This will bring the &#039;Software Update Prefrences&#039; dialog.)<br />\u00a0\u00a0 Go to the &quot;Software Sources&quot; tab and uncheck everything except &#039;Fedora DVD 20 -i386&#039;.<br />\u00a0\u00a0 Click OK and exit the dialog.<br /><br /><b>Step 05:</b> To see what is installable inside the DVD, issue:<br />\u00a0\u00a0<b> $ sudo yum grouplist</b><br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 This will bringup a list of group packages which are either available or already installed.<br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 To install something like the Sugar Desktop Environment, enter the command like this:<br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0<b> $ sudo yum groupinstall &quot;Sugar Desktop Environment&quot;</b><br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 Just replace &quot;Sugar Desktop Environment&quot; with any other string listed by &#039;grouplist&#039; command to install that.<br /><br /><b>Step 06:</b> After finishing installing from that group list, to see what else available within the ISO,<br />\u00a0\u00a0 we need to install &quot;Yumex&quot; - A GUI for YUM.<br /><br /><b>\u00a0\u00a0 $ sudo yum install yumex</b><br />\u00a0\u00a0 <br />\u00a0\u00a0 <b>Note: </b>You will have to enable other repos and the Internet for this download/install to work.<br />\u00a0\u00a0<b> Follow &#039;Step 04&#039;, Check everything else, except &#039;&#039;Fedora DVD 20 -i386&#039; repo.</b><br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 To open YUMEX press &#039;ALT+F2&#039;, and then type: yumex<br />\u00a0\u00a0 <br />\u00a0\u00a0 Go to &#039;Active Reposotories&#039; tab of Yumex and then check only the &quot;fedora-dvd&quot; repo<br />\u00a0\u00a0 After that click on the &#039;Refresh&#039; button to load the list of packages.<br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 Now click the &#039;Available&#039; radio button of Yumex to filter out only the installable packages left in the ISO.<br />\u00a0\u00a0 Dont use the search box, rather manually look for the packages to install and mark them.<br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 After you finish , click on Install. Rest follow the on-screen dialogs.<br /><br /><b>Step 07: </b>After finishing everything, delete the &#039;fedora-dvd.repo&#039;:<br /><b>\u00a0\u00a0 $ sudo rm /etc/yum.repos.d/fedora-dvd.repo</b><br />\u00a0\u00a0 Re-enable all other repos by following the &#039;Step 04&#039;, by doing the reverse of what you did in &#039;Step 04&#039;.<br /><br /><b>Step 08:</b> Delete the mount point.<br />\u00a0\u00a0 <br />\u00a0\u00a0 $ sudo rmdir /mnt/F20_ISO<br />\u00a0\u00a0 <br />Thats all.<br />----------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------<br /><b>3. Install most of the Essential Applications in one Go:</b><br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 $sudo yum install nethogs htop vlc qterminal mousepad ftop audacious-freeworld cairo-dock synapse gpaste beesu bleachbit xine xine-ui xine-plugin knemo shutter lm-sensors xsensors gnome-tweak-tool rekonq goldendict gnome-mplayer conky kolourpaint<br /><br />\u00a0-&gt; Will keep updating this List...<br />\u00a0\u00a0 <br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><b>4. List of Gnome Shell Extensions which are extremely necessery:</b><br />\u00a0\u00a0 Open this link with Firefox- <b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fextensions.gnome.org%2F&amp;h=lAQF3zoba&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" onmouseover=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;https:\\/\\/extensions.gnome.org\\/&quot;);\" onclick=\"LinkshimAsyncLink.swap(this, &quot;https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/l.php?u=https\\u00253A\\u00252F\\u00252Fextensions.gnome.org\\u00252F&amp;h=lAQF3zoba&amp;s=1&quot;);\">https://extensions.gnome.org/</a></b><br />\u00a0\u00a0 Search through these key words in the specified search box.<br /><br />01. NetSpeed<br />02. Gpaste<br />03. Applications Menu<br />04. TaskBar<br />05. Trash<br />06. Advanced Volume Mixer<br />07. Coverflow alt-tab<br />08. Easyscreencast<br />09. Enable log out button on gnome<br />10. Gnote/tomboy integration<br />11. Mediaplayer indicator<br />12. Pidgin conversation indicator<br />13. Places status indicator<br />14. Quicklists<br />15. Topicons<br />16. Uptime indicator<br />17. Workspace indicator<br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />---------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\u00a0\u00a0 <br /></p><br />", "revision": "10154060843995019", "id": "10154060844010019", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/y7/r/8zhNI-VGpiI.png"}